msItem.title: Prologus
msItem.rubric: 1r: In Christi nomine incipit prologus libri Bede presbiteri in libro commentariorum super Marcum

msItem.author: Bede
msItem.title: Commentary on Mark
msItem.incipit: 2v: Omelia lectionis eiusdem uenerabilis Bede presbiteri. Initium evangelii Ihesu Christi
msItem.finalRubric: 102r: Explicit expositio Bede f:i.muli Christi in euangelio secundum marcum

foliation.note: Numbering in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the first leaf of each quire. Full foliation added after digitisation.

collation.p:
The manuscript comprises one quire composed of six leaves followed by eleven quires composed of eight leaves and one quire composed of twelve leaves. There is one leaf cancelled in quire 10 and three leaves cancelled in quire 13.
Quire 16 (ff. 1-6)
Quire 28 (ff. 7-14)
Quire 38 (ff. 15-22)
Quire 48 (ff. 23-30)
Quire 58 (ff. 31-38)
Quire 68 (ff. 39-46)
Quire 78 (ff. 47-54)
Quire 88 (ff. 55-62)
Quire 98 (ff. 63-70)
Quire 108-1 (ff. 71-77: leaf 3 cancelled)
Quire 118 (ff. 78-85)
Quire 128 (ff. 86-93)
Quire 1312-3 (ff. 94-102: leaves 2, 5, 12 cancelled)

p.signatures: Quires are numbered on the verso of the last leaf.

layout.seg: Two columns, 30-34 lines, frame and lines ruled in brown ink. Pricked in the outer margins. Written above top line. Extensions of letters in some of the final lines of columns.

handNote.p: Protogothic bookhand (textualis); '7'- and '9'-shaped diples in the margins.

decoNote.p: Green, red and plain parchment abstract-patterned initial (I, 18 ll., f. 2v), at the opening to the main text.
Green, red and plain parchment initial (I, 21 ll., f. 1r), at the opening to the Prologue.

Red initial (Y, 4 ll., f. 1v) with abstract decoration in red and green, for the opening to the Capitula; red initial (M, 3 ll., f. 97v) with abstract decoration in red and green, with infill of stylized leaf forms in green, for one of the principal openings in the text.
Green and red abstract-patterned initials (e.g. I, 5 ll., f. 35v; I, 6 ll., f. 45r) for some of the paragraph openings.
Red and plain parchment initial (P, 2 ll., f. 6r) for one of the paragraph openings.

Green initials (2 ll.) with simple abstract patterns in red, with no infill, alternating with red initials (2 ll.) with simple abstract patterns in green, for some of the paragraph openings (e.g. ff. 7v-8r); red initials (2 ll.), incorporating abstract and stylized leaf forms, with no infill (e.g. N, 2 ll., f. 11v; E, 2 ll., f. 42r), for some of the paragraph openings.

Red initials (e.g. E, 2 ll., f. 26v; E, 2 ll., f. 37v) on plain parchment inner grounds, with infill of abstract patterns in green, and green initials (2 ll.) with infill of abstract patterns in red (e.g E, 2 ll., f. 76r; E, 2 ll., f. 80v), for some of the paragraph openings.

binding.p: Contemporary alum-tawed skin over wooden boards, with remains of leather strap on the front cover, on four sewing stations. Three nail holes in each corner of front cover which once secured metal bosses; some bronze nails still in place.

history.acquisition: Given to Queens' College Library in the early 1630s by Francis Tyndall Tyndall, Francis with a 17th-century inscription recording the gift on front flyleaf (f. 1r): 'Donum Francisci Tyndall armigeri'.

recordHist.source: This catalogue entry derives predominantly from data assembled for the Fitzwilliam Museum’s Cambridge Illuminations project (publication forthcoming) and draws on the description in M.R. James, A descriptive catalogue of the western manuscripts in the library of Queens’ College, Cambridge (Cambridge, 1905).

availability.p: For further information on the availability of the manuscript, please contact Queens' Old Library and Special Collections.
